<subSubSection id="C36A6543FF9D777C3CADF8C2FA19F87B" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BCF36C8FF9D777C3CADF8C2FDB3F8C9" blockId="0.[151,566,1866,1892]" box="[151,566,1866,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="D08781A4FF9D777C3CADF8C2FDB3F8C9" bold="true" box="[151,566,1866,1892]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3CADF8C2FDB3F8C9" bold="true" box="[151,566,1866,1892]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9D777C3CF5F8C2FE03F8C9" box="[207,390,1866,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3CF5F8C2FE03F8C9" bold="true" box="[207,390,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Delia coarctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCF36C8FF9D777C3CADF81DFA19F87B" blockId="0.[151,1436,1941,2007]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
In this species group, which equals the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9D777C3E43F81DFCB4F803" box="[633,817,1941,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3E43F81DFCB4F803" box="[633,817,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Delia coarctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superspecies’ of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B39FF9D777C3839F81DFB45F802" author="Griffiths" box="[1027,1216,1941,1967]" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" refString="Griffiths, G. C. D. (1991) Anthomyiidae [part]. In: Griffiths, G. C. D. (Ed.), Flies of the Nearctic Region, 8 (2), 8, 1049 - 1240. E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart." type="journal article" year="1991">
Griffiths (
<number id="3DB824EFFF9D777C3842F81DFB32F802" box="[1144,1207,1941,1967]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, belong four presently accepted species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9D777C3D8FF835FD30F87A" authority="Fallen" authorityName="Fallen" box="[437,693,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3D8FF835FDCEF87B" box="[437,587,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D. coarctata</emphasis>
(Fallén)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9D777C3EFFF835FC50F87A" authority="Malloch" authorityName="Malloch" box="[709,981,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3EFFF835FCD6F87B" box="[709,851,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D. montana</emphasis>
(Malloch)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9D777C3FDFF835FABAF87A" authority="Fan, Ma &amp; Li" authorityName="Fan, Ma &amp; Li" box="[997,1343,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3FDFF835FBF0F87B" box="[997,1141,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D. latissima</emphasis>
(Fan, Ma &amp; Li)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9D777C3945F835FA19F87B" box="[1407,1436,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">D.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36A6543FF9C777D3CADFF10FD1CFEFF" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCF36C8FF9C777D3CADFF10FE2CFEAF" blockId="1.[151,1435,152,338]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9C777D3CADFF10FE9AFF1C" box="[151,287,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctoides" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9C777D3CADFF10FE9AFF1C" box="[151,287,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">coarctoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23757A1FF9C777D3D15FF10FE45FF1F" box="[303,448,152,178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. I agree with Griffiths (op. cit.) that the monophyly of the group appears well supported by the characteristic shape of the long surstyli that in caudal view are broad at base but turn very slen­ der distally (
<figureCitation id="134B2A4DFF9C777D3D10FF60FE19FEAF" box="[298,412,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1239,1263]" captionTargetBox="[292,1297,189,1181]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[260,1326,175,1219]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Hypopygium, caudal. 3. Delia coarctoides sp. nov. 4. D. coarctata (Fallén). Notice shape of cercal plate. Same scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175667/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
Figs. 
<number id="3DB824EFFF9C777D3D56FF60FE19FEAF" box="[364,412,232,258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCF36C8FF9C777D3CFCFE98FD1CFEFF" blockId="1.[151,1435,152,338]" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">
The following practical key to the males and females of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D4BFF9C777D3FBFFE98FBB9FE84" box="[901,1084,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Delia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coarctata">
<emphasis id="B904EADAFF9C777D3FBFFE98FBB9FE84" box="[901,1084,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="62">Delia coarctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group uses characters that are normally visible without dissection.
</paragraph>
